#Extract all non-numeric parts of the Budget column
unique_symbols <- unique(gsub("[0-9.,\\s]", "", data$Budget))

#Print symbols

# Setting currency exchange rates
currency_rates <- list(
  "$" = 1,          # US dollar
  "" = 1.1,        # euro -> US dollar
  "" = 1.3,        # pound sterling -> US dollar
  "" = 0.012,      # Indian rupee -> US dollar
  "CA$" = 0.75,     # CAD -> US dollar
  "A$" = 0.70,      # Australian dollar -> US dollar
  "NOK" = 0.1,      # Norwegian Krone -> US dollar
  "SEK" = 0.09,     # Swedish krona -> US dollar
  "CN" = 0.14,     # Chinese Yuan -> US dollar
  "" = 0.14,       # Chinese Yuan -> US dollar
  "" = 0.00075     # South Korean won-> US dollar
)

# Converts Budget to a numeric value (removes currency symbols) and performs unit conversions
data <- data %>%
  mutate(
    # Extract currency symbols
    Currency = trimws(gsub("[0-9.,]", "", Budget)),
    # Extract the numerical part
    Budget_Value = as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9.]", "", Budget)),
    # Harmonize Budget to United States dollars
    Budget_USD = Budget_Value * sapply(Currency, function(x)  {
      if (!is.null(currency_rates[[x]])) currency_rates[[x]] else NA
    })
  )

clean <- data %>% 
  mutate(
    # Clean up and convert the Income column
    gross = as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9]", "", data$Income)), 
     # Clean up and convert the Income column
    budget = as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9]", "", data$Budget)), 
     # Process the Runtime column 
    runtime = as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9]", "", data$Runtime)) 
  )

# Remove lines containing NA
clean <- na.omit(clean)

#  Histograms and box plots of numerical variables
num_vars <- sapply(clean, is.numeric)


for (var in names(clean)[num_vars]) {
  
  data_range <- range(clean[[var]], na.rm = TRUE)
  binwidth_value <- (data_range[2] - data_range[1]) / nclass.FD(clean[[var]])
  #   # Histogram
  p1 <- ggplot(clean, aes_string(x = var)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth = binwidth_value, fill = "blue", color = "black", alpha = 0.7) +
    labs(title = paste("Histogram of", var), x = var, y = "Frequency") +
    theme_minimal() 
  print(p1) 
  
  # box plot 
  p2 <-ggplot(clean, aes_string(y = var)) +
    geom_boxplot(fill = "orange", color = "black", alpha = 0.7) +
    labs(title = paste("Boxplot of", var), y = var) +
    theme_minimal() 
  print(p2)
}
